<HEADLINE> Experts Gather in Ghana to Discuss Poverty Alleviation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Museveni said the password into the next century should
therefore be self-reliance with an emphasis on training of
confident and self-reliant personnel whose objective is to
establish paths instead of following the paved road, a road not
paved by themselves.
</P>
<P>
He drew a relationship between poverty and environmental
deterioration using his country where, he said, 96 percent of
fuel used is wood.
</P>
<P>
He therefore called for a common approach to address
environmental problems of the continent.
</P>
<P>
 IFPRI is aimed at generating information and encouraging
debate to influence action by national governments,
non-governmental organizations, the private sector, international
development institutions and other elements of civil society.
</P>
<P>
In a brief remark, Ghanaian Vice-President John Atta Mills who
is also a member of the Advisory Board cautioned against
complacency by the experts. They must be realistic in their
deliberations, he said. 
</P>
