<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Prepares Guild to Attract Foreign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Investment
Authority said Wednesday that an investment guild which contains
objective and up-to-date information on Ethiopia's investment
opportunities and business climate is under preparation.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a workshop on investment guild and capacity
building here, Abi Woldemeskel, deputy manager of the authority,
said the guild will be a promotional tool that may enable the
country to attract foreign investment, the Ethiopian News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
The deputy manager said the amount of foreign direct investment
Ethiopia has received so far is small compared to the foreign
direct investment received by many developing countries.
</P>
<P>
"There is far less information available to foreign investors
on investment opportunities and conducive business conditions in
Ethiopia than there is for other developing countries," he said.
</P>
<P>
A total of 4,667 investment projects worth of 4.8 billion U.S.
dollars have been approved throughout Ethiopia between May 1992
and September 1998, according to an earlier announcement made by
the authority. However, the majority of the projects were invested
by local investors.
</P>
<P>
Abi said Ethiopia has taken measures to encourage and attract
foreign direct investment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
