<HEADLINE> France Suggests EU Provisionary Administration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 14 (Xinhua) -- France has suggested the creation
of a European Union (EU) provisionary administration in the
Yugoslav province of Kosovo in order to put an end to the crisis
in the Balkans.
</P>
<P>
French President Jacques Chirac said on Tuesday at an EU
informal meeting in Brussels that an international provisionary
administration be created by the United Nations Security Council,
which in its turn should entrust the administration to EU.
</P>
<P>
Chirac said that France supports the proposal by U.N. Secretary
General Kofi Annan that the U.N. Security Council adopt as soon as
possible a resolution under the U.N. Charter Chapter VII, to give
a legal basis to the deployment of an international force in
Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
The French president again stressed the need for NATO to
continue waging the military operation against Yugoslavia, which
he said needs "time and determination."
</P>
<P>
He also suggested that an international conference on the
Balkans be held in a longer term in order to guarantee the
stability of the region and encourage the admission of the Balkan
countries to the EU.  
</P>
</TEXT>
