<HEADLINE> Iran's Industrial Exports Falls by 14.2 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Iran said on Wednesday that it earned
more than 971 million U.S. dollars from exports of industrial products
during the past Iranian calendar year (ended March 20), showing a fall
of 14.2 percent from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian Industries Ministry said in a report that auto
industries topped in industrial exports with a 74.8 percent growth and
its income stood at 23 million dollars in the period, the Islamic
Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The export of electronic products followed the list with 30.9
percent growth and its earning at 5.1 million dollars, while export of
non-metallic minerals gained 26.3 percent growth, reaching 52 million
dollars.
</P>
<P>
However, export of textiles and garments showed about 59.8 percent
decrease, earning 131 million dollars, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
