<HEADLINE> Mozambican President Calls for Re-defining of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican President Joaquim
Chissano Wednesday called on re-defining of the functions and
objectives of universities in a bid to adapt to changes now
challenging the world.
</P>
<P>
He made the call at the opening of the ninth meeting of
Association of Portuguese Language Universities.
</P>
<P>
Chissano said the challenge now facing high education is how to
re- define its functions and objectives in this ever-changing
world so as to help solve the pressing issues in social life.
</P>
<P>
The president believed that higher education must show more
concern to the "loftiest" ideals, which are tolerance, peace,
democracy and peaceful co-existence among different peoples, to
rid the humanity of war and other conflicts and promote steady
development.
</P>
<P>
Cooperation among Portuguese speaking countries in higher
education is of great importance to training researchers,
professors and other professionals who are conducive to the
development of these countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
He hoped the meeting will be a milestone in the relations
among Portuguese speaking countries which are making efforts in
establishing new cooperation mode.
</P>
<P>
The three-day meeting, with a theme of "universities and
changes", has drawn over 200 people from countries and regions
including Angola, Brazil, Portugal, Cape Verde, Guinea Bissau,
Mozambique, Sao Tome &AMP; Principe and Macau.
</P>
<P>
The association which was founded in Praia, capital of Cape
Verde, in 1986, now groups 136 institutions, including those from
non-Portuguese- speaking countries who are related to the language
in terms of culture or academia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
