<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Germany Loses Two Unmanned Planes on Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bonn, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The German forces have lost 2
unmanned reconnaissance planes during the operations in Kosovo
since this Monday, a Defense Ministry official said Wednesday in
Bonn.
</P>
<P>
One of the two Drone unmanned planes, each costing 2 million
marks, did not return from a Wednesday morning reconnaissance
mission over Kosovo and another has missed since Monday, State
Secretary of Defense Ministry Peter Wichert said.
</P>
<P>
The Defense Ministry did not confirm whether the planes had
</P>
<P>
been shot down by the Yugoslav troops as Belgrade had reported.
</P>
<P>
The plane is able to fly at an altitude between 300 to 600
meters high and take photos during its operations, Von Kirchbach,
General Inspector of German forces said. 
