<HEADLINE> Romania on Yugoslavia's Possible Adhesion to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslavia's possible adhesion
to the Russia-Belarus Union "must not affect" Romania's objective
of integration with NATO and EU structures, said on Wednesday the
Romanian Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Simona Miculescu.
</P>
<P>
The working mechanism of the respective union "is not in a
state of institutionalization advanced enough in order to be able
to speak of this structure in terms of an efficient operation'',
stressed the spokeswoman, adding that by this unilateral decision
of the Belgrade parliament one cannot anticipate yet all
political, economic or military implications.
</P>
<P>
If such a political union had a finality, the Romanian Foreign
Ministry thinks its forms of action "must not affect" the
fundamental objective of the Romanian foreign policy, meaning the
integration with the European and Euro-Atlantic structures, Simona
Miculescu said.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian Foreign Ministry will carefully watch the future
political developments, she concluded.  
