<HEADLINE> Russia Uneasy Over Pakistan's Missile Test-firing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Russia feels uneasy over
Pakistan's test-firing of a Ghauri-II (HAFT-V) ballistic missile
Wednesday morning, a tit-for-tat response to India's Agni-II
ballistic missile test-firing on Sunday, the Russian Foreign
Ministry said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A statement by the ministry said Russia believes that Pakistan
and other parties concerned should stop developing ballistic
missiles that are capable of carrying nuclear warheads.
</P>
<P>
The fact that countries in the South Asian Sub-Continent began
to own intermediate-range missiles runs counter to the interest of
nuclear non-proliferation and nuclear disarmament, as well as to
the positive development of the situation in the region, the
ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The ministry issued a similar statement on Tuesday to condemn
India's test-firing of a ballistic missile on Sunday, calling
India's move detrimental to the stability of the region. 
