manufacturing plant in Nantong, Jiangsu Province, China.
</P>
<P>
The plant, which is expected on-stream by 2001, will have a
capacity of 6,000 tonnes per annum. The project will make use of
state-of-the-art technology developed by Zeneca and will operate
to the highest international safety and environmental standards.
</P>
<P>
It will manufacture the herbicide paraquat, the active
ingredient in 'Gramoxone', one of Zeneca's leading herbicide
brands and one of the world's biggest selling crop protection
products.
</P>
<P>
Michel Maisonnial, Chairman of Zeneca China Ltd. commented:
"There is a well established and growing demand for 'Gramoxone' in
China which is currently met by imports."
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese herbicide market is currently valued at USD 450
million and has been growing by 20 percent a year over the last
five years.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture company, Zeneca Nantong Agrochemical Company,
will own and operate the plant. Zeneca's partners in the joint
venture are Nantong Pesticide Company, Jiangsu Agrochemical
Company and the Nantong Petrochemical Company.
</P>
<P>
Zeneca Agrochemicals is the crop protection and plant science
business of AstraZeneca. It is the third largest supplier to this
international market, with sales in 1998 of 2.88 billion U.S.
dollars in over 130 countries and areas. 
