"developed a tremendous military interest in Kenya following last
August's bombing blast at its embassy in Nairobi."
</P>
<P>
The annual exercise since 1996 is being held in Isiolo town,
home to three military schools and the 78th Armored Brigade, said
the information officer.
</P>
<P>
Simani also dismissed the report which said the exercise will
extend to the Kenyan border with Ethiopia as "completely wrong",
saying the area of the exercise is in the middle of Kenya and far
from borders.
</P>
<P>
The main activities of the exercise are focused on civic
assistance to local communities and medical service to the Kenyan
army, said Simani.
</P>
<P>
About 11 American doctors joined the exercise in Isiolo town,
according to the press office of the Department of Defense.
</P>
<P>
The Eastern African newspaper said earlier that an official at
the U. S. embassy in Nairobi believed the U.S. troops would gain
valuable experience from the joint exercise.
</P>
<P>
The official was quoted as saying that North Eastern Kenya and
the adjacent areas were "very useful to the (U.S.) military since
we do not have such terrain in our country." 
</P>
