<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Warships to Pass Turkish Straits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The General Staff of the Turkish Armed Forces said in a statement
that three Russian warships in the first batch will pass the Canakkale
and Bosphorus Straits into the Adriatic Sea between April 15 and 16,
other three in the second batch will pass through April 18 and 19 and
the last three in the third batch will pass through between April 21
and 22.
</P>
<P>
A Russian reconnaissance warship passed through the Turkish
straits into the Adriatic Sea early this month with a mission to
monitor air strikes by the North Atlantic Treaty Organization
(NATO) against Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The Russian embassy in Ankara presented two requests for the
passage of the Russian warships through the Turkish straits and the
Turkish government has given the green light.
</P>
<P>
The passage of foreign warships through the Turkish straits is
overseen by the 1936 Treaty of Montreux.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the Black Sea littoral states can sail their
ships through the straits when they inform Turkish authorities of
their intentions at least eight days in advance.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the Russian warships would be carrying out
"reconnaissance tasks" in the war zone of the NATO air strikes against
Yugoslavia, which have been going on for more than 20 days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
