<HEADLINE> U.N. Concerned at Humanitarian Situation in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Security Council on Wednesday expressed its concern over the grave
humanitarian situation in Kosovo, the Federal Republic of
Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The Security Council was briefed this morning on the
developments of the humanitarian situation in Kosovo and in its
region by Mr. Martin Griffiths, Deputy to the U.N.
Under-Secretary-General for Humanitarian Affairs.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to the press, Council President for the current month
Alain Dejammet of France said members of the Council were
determined to continue to follow closely the development of the
situation in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Members of the Council reiterated their support for the work of
the humanitarian agencies, in particular the Office of the United
Nations High Commissioner for Refugees, as lead agency.
</P>
<P>
Members of the Council invited all parties to ensure the safety
of the humanitarian personnel. 
</P>
