<HEADLINE> Egypt's Free Zone Exports Rise by 32 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The industrial exports of Egypt's free
zones rised by 32 percent in the first quarter this year over
the same period last year, an official in charge of free zone
issues said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Egypt's free zones exported 120 million U.S. dollars worth of
industrial goods from January to March in 1999, 2 9 million dollars
more than those in the same period in 1998, Chairman of the General
Authority and Free Zones Ibrahim Fawzi told reporters.
</P>
<P>
Fawzi made the remarks after a visit to the free zone in the town
of Nasr near Cairo, where he placed a foundation stone for expansions
of an industrial project producing ingredients for soft drinks.
</P>
<P>
Egypt has set up several free zones and industrial parks in
Cairo, Alexandria, Ismailia, Suez, Port Said and Dumyat. Investors
enjoy preferential conditions for investing in the free zones.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian official said the exports in March alone increased by
34 percent to 48.7 percent compared to the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
The imports from the local markets by investors in the free zones
soared by 12 percent to 28.3 million dollars in the first quarter of
1999 from the same period of 1998, he added.

NNNN
04:47 04:47 g # PAB
