<HEADLINE> UNDP Helping Africa Reduce Small Arms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 15 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Development Program (UNDP) is providing funds to help 16 West
African countries implement an arms moratorium, according to a
UNDP press release reaching here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The arms moratorium has been launched as part of UNDP's
efforts to address security challenges in the region.
</P>
<P>
The goal of the 13 million U.S. dollar program to which UNDP
contributes 2.1 million dollars, is to reduce the number of small
arms and weapons that fuel the region's conflicts.
</P>
<P>
In cooperation with the Organization of African Unity and the
Economic Commission of West African States, UNDP will establish
arms databases, train security forces, review legislation
governing the purchase of small arms and collect and destroy
weapons, among others.  
</P>
</TEXT>
