<HEADLINE> HK Hopes For More Construction Cooperation With Mainland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Kwong Hon-sang, the secretary for
works of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, said here
today that he hopes there will be more cooperation in the
construction sector with the mainland.
</P>
<P>
Better use could be made of Hong Kong's management experience
and the mainland's manpower, Kwong told a seminar on the
construction industry and urban-rural planning.
</P>
<P>
He said that people in the construction industry in Hong Kong
have shown great enthusiasm and hope to bid for projects in a just
and open way.
</P>
<P>
Although the mainland and Hong Kong have different controls on
engineering and construction, the mainland has improved a great
deal in recent years by studying management techniques in foreign
countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
Kwong led a 97-member delegation to Beijing for the '99
Mainland and Hong Kong Seminar on Management in the Engineering
and Construction Industry and Urban-Rural Planning, which is
scheduled for April 14-16.
</P>
<P>
Delegation members include SAR officials, education and
institute professionals, and people from private construction
companies in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The seminar was organized by China's Construction Ministry, the
Works Bureau, and the Planning, Environment and Lands Bureau of
Hong Kong to provide an arena for discussing management of the
engineering and construction industry and urban and rural planning.
</P>
<P>
After the seminar, some delegation members will visit Hebei
Province for discussions with the Provincial Construction
Commission about sewage treatment and residential housing
construction and will visit some infrastructure facilities.
</P>
