<HEADLINE> Dhaka to Host Global Tiger Forum Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh will host a conference
of the Global Tiger Forum in November this year, the official BSS
news agency reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The meeting of the forum, comprising 14 countries, is part of
extending international cooperation for preserving wild lives.
</P>
<P>
The decision of hosting the conference came at an
inter-ministerial meeting held here on Thursday at the Ministry of
Forest and Environment, which also decided to constitute a
five-member working committee to arrange the conference.
</P>
<P>
The meeting also discussed the scope for international
cooperation in preserving the sanctuary of tigers in the
Sundarbans in southwestern Bangladesh and other areas of the
country, and the development of its management aspect, the BSS
said.
</P>
<P>
The population of Bengal tigers is decreasing rapidly following
poaching and shrinking of livable spaces inside the Sundarbans,
their major sanctuaries in the country.
</P>
<P>
Since the turn of this century, the habitat and number of
Bengal tigers have been reduced by some 95 percent, experts said.
</P>
