<HEADLINE> 7 Killed in Philippines' Road Mishap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Seven people were killed and more
than 20 others injured when a passenger bus and a passenger
jeepney collided head-on along a highway in Barangay Madong,
Janiuay town of the central Philippines on Thursday morning.
</P>
<P>
A report of the Philippines News Agency said a three-year-old
girl was among the dead.
</P>
<P>
A total of 23 people were injured and they were rushed to the
nearby hospital, where they were now declared out of danger by
their attending physicians.
</P>
<P>
The 30-year-old driver of the passenger jeepney is presently
being treated for bruises and injuries in different parts of his
body.
</P>
<P>
The report said the bus was speeding on its way from Iloilo
City to Calinog town when it collided head-on with the
passenger-laden jeepney and plowed it down the road several
meters. The jeepney was in total wreck with its canopy separated
from its body.
</P>
<P>
The bus driver escaped from the scene and is now the subject of
a hunt launched by the Janiuay police. 
