<HEADLINE> Chinese Infant Congenital Heart Disease Research Center In Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 15 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Infant Congenital
Heart Disease Research Institute has been set up at the Shanghai
Children's Medical Research Center as the first of its kind in
China.
</P>
<P>
It is expected to improve the diagnosis and treatment of the
disease. There are 100,000 to 150,000 children born with
congenital heart disease in China every year.
</P>
<P>
One study of 20,000 new-born babies showed an incidence of the
disease of 6.7 per thousand. But, even though China has 300
hospitals that can perform operations on children suffering from
the disease, only 30,000 infants have the operation each year.
</P>
