Hind Ho led gainers of the day increasing by 73 cents to close
at 2.59 Singapore dollars. Bukit Sem gained 70 cents to finish at
12.30 Singapore dollars. CityDev was 55 cents higher to end at
10.50 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, KepCorp led the losers of the day shedding 44
cents to close at 4.66 Singapore dollars. Asean fell 40 cents to
end at 7.10 U.S. dollars. SIA F lose 40 cents to finish at 13.80
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that the market finally caved to profit-taking in
morning trading, but it staged a comeback in the afternoon on the
back of hopes that banks will cut prime lending rates.
</P>
<P>
They noted that the rebound in the afternoon was led by
property stocks, which rose with the hope of lower interest rates
which would make property purchases more affordable. 
</P>
</TEXT>
