<HEADLINE> Korean Air Cargo Plane Crashes in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 15 (Xinhua) -- A Korean Air cargo plane crashed
here this afternoon shortly after take-off, killing three migrant
construction workers on the ground and injuring 26 others,
including six seriously injured with a further two in a critical
condition.
</P>
<P>
There is no report about the crew members on board. Concerned
figures estimate that there is little hope for their survival.
</P>
<P>
The MD-11 cargo plane, which took off at 16:04 at the Shanghai
Hongqiao Airport en route for Seoul, dropped immediately from an
elevation of 1,000 meters onto a construction site in the Minhang
District of Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Cargo and wreckage were scattered over some 1,000 sq meters,
according to eye-witnesses.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the Shanghai municipal government, the local
aviation department and public security bureau rushed to the
accident site.
</P>
<P>
The injured workers have been sent to the central hospital in
Minhang.  
</P>
