<HEADLINE> Angola Says UNITA Kills 6 NGO Representatives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Angolan government announced here
Thursday that the rebel UNITA forces had attacked a car along a
road in Kuanza-Sul Province in northern Angola, killing all six
foreign and local non- governmental organization (NGO)
representatives in the car.
</P>
<P>
The NGO delegates were on their way Wednesday to Sumbe, capital
of Kuanza-Sul to attend a United Nations Food Program meeting on
issues concerning humanitarian assistance to Angola's increasing
refugees when the car they were in was attacked by "terrorists" of
the National Union for the Total Independence of Angola, the
official Angola News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The Land-rover they were travelling in exploded on impact,
killing all six on board.
</P>
<P>
Sources from local police said the dead were "almost burned to
charcoal".
</P>
<P>
So far, three of the dead have been identified as Duotor
Ferreira, Save the Children (Italy) representative in the
province, Narciso Xavier and Manuel Gabriel from Angola's Youth
Christian Association. The names and affiliation of the other
three are yet to be found out. 
</P>
