<HEADLINE> hke041555 -3 Robbers Killed in Gunbattle With Philippine Officers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Three of four highway robbers were
killed while a civilian, a Marine soldier and a policeman were
wounded in a four-hour running gunbattle which occurred at a
residential area in Cotabato City of southern Philippines Thursday
morning.
</P>
<P>
Police in Cotabato City said they were yet in the process of
identifying the slain suspects. One of the robbers managed to
escape, the Philippines News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the incident started at 5:15 a.m.
local time shortly after the robbers, posing as passengers, held
up a passenger van along a street of Cotabato City.
</P>
<P>
Alert bystanders and robbery victims immediately informed
police of the incident and police began chasing the fleeing
suspects.
</P>
<P>
In the pursuit operation, firefight caused the wounding of a
policeman and the slaying of the three suspects. A Marine trooper
and a civilian were also wounded in the firefight.
</P>
<P>
Police recovered from the suspects four bags filled with their
loot, two revolvers and a dagger. 
</P>
