</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990415.0129 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wrap-up: FM Spokesman's Statement at Press Conference (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
When it comes to the current situation in Malaysia, Sun said
that as a friendly neighbor of Malaysia, China hopes that "
Malaysia could maintain political stability and develop its
economy as fast as possible."
</P>
<P>
Sun made the remarks when asked to comment on the sentence of
ousted Malaysian Deputy Prime Minister Anwar Ibrahim to six years
in prison Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
China also demanded seriously that the US Government express
explicitly its opposition to resolutions concerning Taiwan that
were passed recently in the US Senate and House of Representatives,
according to the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
"We demand that the US government strictly adhere to the
principles laid down in the three Sino-US joint communiques and
the relevant commitments made by the US side, so as to prevent the
Taiwan issue from disturbing the development of Sino-US relations,
" said Sun.
</P>
<P>
The US Senate and House of representatives have recently passed
a resolution commemorating the 20th anniversary of the so-called "
Taiwan Relations Act". The Senate also passed "the Resolution
Relating to Taiwan's Participation in the World Health
Organization."
</P>
<P>
"Taiwan is a province of China," Sun said. "As an internal
affair of China, the Taiwan question brooks no interference of any
foreign country," he reiterated.
</P>
<P>
In 1979, the US side violated the principles of "the Joint
Communique on the Establishment of Diplomatic Relation Between
China and the US" by cooking up a so-called "Taiwan Relations Act"
in an attempt to legalize its action in using the Taiwan question
to interfere in China's internal affairs through a US domestic
legislature, he said.
</P>
<P>
Sun emphasized that "the Chinese Government has always stood
firmly opposed to this erroneous practice on the US side."
</P>
<P>
Not long ago, the US congress passed a resolution commemorating
the 20th anniversary of the so-called "Taiwan Relations Act,"
which constitutes a grave violation of the three joint communiques
between China and the US, and a flagrant interference in China's
internal affairs, he said.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese side hereby expresses its strong resentment and
firm opposition to it," Sun stressed.
</P>
<P>
As known to all, he said, the World Health Organization is an
inter-governmental organization composed only of sovereign states.
As part of China, "Taiwan has no right whatsoever to accede to it.
"
</P>
<P>
Acting in disregard of the basic norms governing international
relations and the principles enshrined in the three joint
communiques between China and the US, the US Senate passed the so-
called "Resolution Relating to Taiwan's Participation in the World
Health Organization."
</P>
<P>
Talking about Yasser Arafat's current visit, Sun voiced his
belief here that "the visit will help promote bilateral friendship
and cooperation in various fields."
</P>
<P>
Arafat, president of the Palestine state and chairman of the
executive committee of the Palestine Liberation Organization, has
arrived in China, he said, and that meetings between Arafat and
Chinese leaders have been arranged.
</P>
<P>
Both sides will exchange views on issues of common concern,
such as bilateral relations and situation in the Middle East,
especially the Middle East peace process, according to Sun.
</P>
<P>
Sun refused to give a definite answer when asked here to
confirm if Vice-Premier Qian Qichen will visit Macao on April 20.
</P>
<P>
"Qian is mainly in charge of China's foreign relations, as well
as Taiwan, Hong Kong and Macao affairs, "Sun said. "Qian paid a
visit to Macao recently, and will visit Macao in the future."
</P>
<P>
Sun added that Qian's visit to Macao will be announced if
decided.
</P>
<P>
He said that China supports the process of the ASEM meeting and
will actively take part in its follow-up actions.
</P>
<P>
Relevant countries, in the spirit of mutual respect, equality
and reciprocity, have pushed forward a cooperative momentum
between Asian and European nations since the first ASEM summit
meeting was held in Bangkok in 1996, according to Sun.
</P>
<P>
The follow-up actions set at the meeting have been proceeding
well, he said, adding that this demonstrates the common aspiration
of Asian and European nations to focus their attention on economic,
scientific and technological cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan announced,
at the just-concluded second ASEM Foreign Ministers' Meeting,
China's decision to donate 500,000 US dollars to the ASEM Trust
Fund and to host the third ASEM Foreign Ministers' Meeting in the
year 2001.
</P>
<P>
According to the spokesman, the ASEM meeting for ministers of
science and technology will be held in Beijing next October.
</P>
<P>
He said China hopes that ASEM members would strictly abide by
the common grounds reached at the two ASEM summit meetings and
promote the ASEM meeting in a healthy way.  
</P>
</TEXT>
