<HEADLINE> Egypt Praised for Helping Keep Sudan's Stability </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Sudanese Foreign Minister Mustafa
Osman Ismail Thursday hailed Egypt's role in helping maintain the
stability of the country.
</P>
<P>
Egypt also plays a pivotal role in facing up to conspiracies
threatening Sudan's unity and security, Ismail said during a
stopover at Cairo.
</P>
<P>
Egypt has been working to help Sudan achieve national
reconciliation, he said, expressing hope that this effort would
yield tangible results.
</P>
<P>
Stability and security in both Egypt and Sudan will further
promote Arab reconciliation, solidarity and Security, and enhance
the development process in Africa, the minister said.
</P>
<P>
Sudan has been bogged down in a civil war since 1983 when rebel
groups took up arms to fight against the Muslim government for
greater autonomy for the southern provinces, which are mainly
Christian, animist and African.
</P>
<P>
Egypt has been keeping contacts with Sudan's opposition groups,
including the southern rebel factions and the northern Muslim
opposition leaders, calling for solutions to the Sudanese conflict
in a bid to maintain the country's integration.
</P>
<P>
Egypt fears that a possible disintegration of Sudan would
endanger the Nile, its main water sources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
