<HEADLINE> International Seminar on China's Largest Ethnic Group Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, April 15 (Xinhua) -- An international seminar on the
Zhuang ethnic group, the largest minority of china's 55 ethnic
groups, opened today in Nanning, capital of south China's Guangxi
Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Scholars and experts from China and a dozen of countries
worldwide including Vietnam, the United States, Japan, Australia,
Laos and Thailand are attending the four day event between June 15-
18.
</P>
<P>
The experts will discuss the ethnic group's history and
traditional culture of the past as well as its economic and social
development in modern times.
</P>
<P>
Approximately 15 million of the 18 million members of the
Zhuang ethnic group live in compact communities in Guangxi.
</P>
