<BODY>
<HEADLINE> FM Spokesman: China Opposes US Resolution on Taiwan (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 15 (Xinhua) -- China demanded today that the US
Government express explicitly its opposition to resolutions
concerning Taiwan that were passed recently in the US Senate and
House of Representatives.
</P>
<P>
"We demand that the US government strictly adhere to the
principles laid down in the three Sino-US joint communiques and
the relevant commitments made by the US side, so as to prevent the
Taiwan issue from disturbing the development of Sino-US relations,
" said Foreign Ministry Spokesman Sun Yuxi at a routine press
conference here today.
</P>
<P>
The US Senate and House of representatives have recently passed
a resolution commemorating the 20th anniversary of the so-called "
Taiwan Relations Act". The Senate also passed "the Resolution
Relating to Taiwan's Participation in the World Health
Organization."
</P>
<P>
"Taiwan is a province of China," Sun said. "As an internal
affair of China, the Taiwan question brooks no interference of any
foreign country," the spokesman reiterated.
</P>
<P>
In 1979, the US side violated the principles of "the Joint
Communique on the Establishment of Diplomatic Relation Between
China and the US" by cooking up a so-called "Taiwan Relations Act"
in an attempt to legalize its action in using the Taiwan question
to interfere in China's internal affairs through a US domestic
legislature, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990415.0151 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> FM Spokesman: China Opposes US Resolution on Taiwan (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sun emphasized that "the Chinese Government has always stood
firmly opposed to this erroneous practice on the US side."
</P>
<P>
Not long ago, the US congress passed a resolution commemorating
the 20th anniversary of the so-called "Taiwan Relations Act,"
which constitutes a grave violation of the three joint communiques
between China and the US, and a flagrant interference in China's
internal affairs, he said.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese side hereby expresses its strong resentment and
firm opposition to it," Sun stressed.
</P>
<P>
As known to all, he said, the World Health Organization is an
inter-governmental organization composed only of sovereign states.
As part of China, "Taiwan has no right whatsoever to accede to it.
"
</P>
<P>
Acting in disregard of the basic norms governing international
relations and the principles enshrined in the three joint
communiques between China and the US, the US Senate passed the so-
called "Resolution Relating to Taiwan's Participation in the World
Health Organization."
</P>
<P>
Sun noted that "the Chinese side is firmly opposed to it."
</P>
