Ecevit denied the report that the North Atlantic Treaty
Organization has officially asked Turkey to fully participate in the
bombardment of Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
As a member state of NATO, Turkey has been supporting the military
alliance's air strikes against Yugoslavia since march 24.
</P>
<P>
Turkey has 11 F-16 fighters stationed at the Ghedy air base in
northern Italy for defensive missions to protect the large bombers of
NATO in air strikes against Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Ecevit said that as a Balkan Country, it would be risky for Turkey
to participate in NATO bombardment of Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Turkish Foreign Ministry deputy spokesman Sermet Atacanli also
ruled out such a request for Turkey to fully participate in NATO
bombardment. 
</P>
