<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IFAC 14th World Congress to be Held in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 15 (Xinhua) -- The International Federation of
Automatic Controls (IFAC) 14th World Congress will be held in
Beijing from July 5-9, organizers said here today.
</P>
<P>
About 1,300 scientists and technologists in this field are
expected to attend the congress scheduled for a developing country
for the first time.
</P>
<P>
The congress will cover areas including manufacturing, controls
design, systems and signals, life-support systems, industrial
application, transportation systems, systematic engineering and
management, according to Sun Bolin, secretary-general of the
congress' organizing committee.
</P>
<P>
"Academic activities including lectures, paper exchanges,
symposiums and exhibitions will be held during the congress," he
said.
</P>
<P>
He told a press conference here today that nearly 2,200 papers
from 68 countries and regions have been submitted for possible
presentation at the congress. More than 1,550 papers have been
accepted covering the entire spectrum of the control field.
</P>
<P>
The IFAC, founded in 1957, aims to promote the scientific
research and technological development in the field of automatic
control and applications in the broadest sense in all systems,
including engineering, physical, biological, environmental, social,
economic and computational sectors.
</P>
<P>
The number of its membership countries has been increased from
18 in 1957 to the current 50. It holds a world congress every
three years. The federation's current president is Lu Yongzai, a
well-known Chinese expert in the automation field.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
