<HEADLINE> Independent Foreign Policy of Peace: China's Choice </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Experts attending a symposium on
"world security and China" pointed out here today that at the
present stage, the independent foreign policy of peace is still
China's natural choice.
</P>
<P>
Dozens of experts on international relations from China's
leading research organizations participated in the symposium,
which was hosted by the Foreign Affairs College.
</P>
<P>
Focusing on the strategic adjustments for world security since
the end of the cold war and especially the new changes in world
security mechanisms in recent years, experts discussed the new
challenges facing the security of China, the Asia-Pacific region,
and the world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
They also looked at ways to ensure peace and security for the
next century.
</P>
<P>
Experts agreed that by actively advocating the independent
foreign policy of peace since the end of the cold war, China has
upgraded its strategic position in the world arena, and played an
active role in creating a peaceful environment for the Asia-
Pacific region.  
</P>
