<HEADLINE> Killed in Philippines' Explosion Up to 12 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MANILA, April 15 (Xinhua) -- The death toll of the bomb
explosion in a crowded dancing hall in Philippines' Southeastern
Albay province early Thursday increased to 12 and the wounded are
about 50, the Philippine News Agency reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The blast, believed to be coming from a home-made molotov type
bomb rocked the otherwise peaceful and gay celebration for the
patron of Barangay Ligwan, an interior village of Rapurapu town,
sending slivers of irons and glass shrapnells, and splatters of
flesh and blood in pandemonium.
</P>
<P>
Ten of those seriously wounded were either declared dead on
arrival or have expired while undergoing treatment at various
clinics in Albay, majority of whom were brought to the Bicol
Regional Training and Teaching Hospital in Legazpi City, three or
four hours travel by sea and land from the spot.
</P>
<P>
At least five more victims are in serious condition at the
hospital.
</P>
<P>
Police investigators said they still face a blank wall on the
massacre.
</P>
<P>
An earlier report said some of the fatalities and wounded were
vacationers from Metro Manila. 
</P>
