<DOCNO> XIE19990415.0176 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> BOC Supports Loss-Making SOEs with Closed-End Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Sources from the Bank of China (
BOC) said today that the BOC had granted closed-end loans of 2.98
billion yuan and 4.3 million U.S. dollars by the end of February
to help loss-making state-owned enterprises (SOEs) overcome their
difficulties.
</P>
<P>
Of these loans, 1.76 billion yuan and 3.08 million U.S. dollars
went to 178 foreign-trade enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Closed-end loans are loans earmarked for funding specific
projects, and the debtors are not allowed to use the capital for
purposes other than these pre-designated projects.
</P>
<P>
Sources said the BOC has detailed regulations governing these
loans in order to minimize financial risk.
</P>
<P>
Strict management measures have thus far yielded good results,
according to the sources.
</P>
<P>
The BOC provided 120 million yuan in closed-end loans to the
Chifeng Foreign Trade Corporation in the Inner Mongolia Autonomous
Region to purchase cashmere, helping the company to grow rapidly.
The BOC now has recovered all of the closed-end loans it provided
to Chifeng, as well as 8.6 million yuan from old loans to the
company.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
