<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT, April 15 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN -- Gregor Gysi, first German mediator to Belgrade,
briefed the press on his talks with Yugoslav President Slobodan
Milosevic on Wednesday, saying Milosevic would like to negotiate
directly with Kosovo ethnic Albanian leaders under the mediation
of U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan.
</P>
<P>
Gysi, parliamentary chairman of the Democratic Socialist Party
(DSP) group who returned here after his one-day trip to Yugoslavia,
said Milosevic promised that all Kosovar refugees fleeing NATO
airstrikes could return home in the near future. Yugoslavia sticks
to its stance of refusing forces of NATO and the United Nations to
enter Kosovo, except for UN civilian observers, he added. (Germany-
Yugoslavia-Milosevic)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BELGRADE -- Since NATO began air strikes against Yugoslavia on
March 24, four NATO fighter planes and two helicopters have
crashed in Bosnian territory with 37 U.S. airborne servicemen
killed, the Serb TV station reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The TV station quoted an unidentified senior official with the
NATO-led Multinational Stabilization Force in Bosnia as saying
that only at 10 a.m. Wednesday morning, a NATO fighter plane,
which was hit by Yugoslav anti-air fire, crashed in the Gorazde
region. At nearly the same time, another NATO fighter plane,
reportedly hit by Yugoslav anti-air forces, crashed in Majevica
while struggling to fly back to the airport in Tuzla, the TV
station said. (Kosovo-NATO-Planes)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- Pakistan successfully test-fired a Shaheen-I
ballistic missile Thursday morning, about 24 hours after its
launching of a Ghauri-II missile, a Foreign Office statement said.
</P>
<P>
The Shaheen ballistic missile was test-fired at 09:50 a.m.
local time (0450 GMT) from a site near Pakistan's southern port
city of Karachi, an official from the Pakistan Atomic Energy
Commission told Xinhua. Shaheen, with a range of 600 kilometers,
employs a solid fuel motor and can be tipped with any type of
warhead, the statement said. (Pakistan-Missile-Test)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BOSTON -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji's visit to the United
States has achieved positive results as had been expected, Chinese
Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan said on Wednesday at the end of the
visit.
</P>
<P>
The positive results have been achieved through frank and
candid talks and discussions between Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji
and U.S. President Bill Clinton and other leaders during the eight
days of the visit in six cities, Tang told reporters. Tang, who
accompanied Premier Zhu in the entire trip, summed up four results
of Premier Zhu's visit. (US-China-Visit) 
</P>
</TEXT>
