<HEADLINE> China, France Can Cooperate Well in Many Aspects: Vice-Premier (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo said here
Thursday at an annual Sino-French Economic Seminar that China and
France can cooperate well in many economic sectors.
</P>
<P>
"China and France are highly complementary in their economy,"
he said in a speech at the opening ceremony of the 5th Sino-French
Economic Seminar.
</P>
<P>
"The areas of agriculture, energy, aviation, space technology,
transport, telecommunications, chemicals and capital raising where
France enjoys internationally advanced technology and products,
are just the fields China considers a priority in its economic
expansion," he said.
</P>
<P>
Jointly launched by the China Council for the Promotion of
International Trade (CCPIT) and the France-China Committee of
France, the seminar is attracting more than 300 French and Chinese
officials and businessmen. They are expected to make discussions
on speed trains, insurance, intellectual property rights and
environmental protection during the two-day session.
</P>
<P>
France is a leading export market for China in Europe. It is
one of the major sources of imports in terms of advanced
technology and complete sets of equipment, the vice-premier noted.
</P>
<P>
Trade volume between China and France reached a record high of
six billion plus US dollars in 1998, up 8 percent on 1997. France
is the 10th largest foreign investor for China. The number of
France-invested projects hit 1,400, involving a contractual
investment of 4.6 billion US dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
