<HEADLINE> Hughes Electronics First-Quarter Profits Rise 76 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Hughes Electronics Corp. said
Wednesday that its first-quarter net income rose by 76 percent as
revenues were boosted by growth in subscribers for its DirecTV
satellite television service.
</P>
<P>
A report from the company said the first-quarter profits rose
to 78.3 million U.S. dollars, up from 44.5 million dollars a year
earlier. Revenues rose 12.5 percent to 1.45 billion dollars from 1.
29 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
"Our leadership in the direct-to-home market is a key growth
and value driver for Hughes," Michael Smith, chairman of the
company, said in a statement. "Our revenue growth was driven by
continued record DirecTV subscriber growth," he added.
</P>
<P>
First-quarter revenues for Hughes direct-to-home satellite
broadcast business rose 43.5 percent to 556.6 million dollars, up
from 387.9 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Domestic DirecTV business revenues rose 34 percent to 474
million dollars, with 304,000 new subscribers added in the quarter,
bringing the total to 4.76 million.
</P>
<P>
Latin American DirecTV revenues nearly doubled to 61 million
dollars, up from 31 million dollars a year earlier, with 70,000
new subscribers added to bring the total to 554,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
