<HEADLINE> Malaria Kills 14 People in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Fourteen people so far have died
in Benane division of Garissa District in Kenya's North Eastern
Province following an outbreak of malaria in the area.
</P>
<P>
Kenyan Health Minister Jackson Kalweo Wednesday told the
parliament that the government had taken steps to curb the spread
of the epidemic in the area.
</P>
<P>
Kelweo said most of those who had so far died were children,
adding that about 200 people were currently affected by the
outbreak, he was quoted by the People newspaper as saying
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
However, the minister said that a contingent of district health
 management team member had already visited the area and were
still there offering treatment to the victims.
</P>
<P>
Kalweo noted that the delay of dispatching personnel and drugs
to the affected area was caused by the poor communication network
in the region, saying that to curb the situation, the government
was in the process of putting up drug stores in the two northern
frontier districts of Wajir and Garissa in the North Eastern
Province. 
</P>
