<HEADLINE> TV Series to Draw Laughter and Tears from Audience </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 15 (Xinhua) -- China Central Television Station
(CCTV) and many other TV stations have their eyes on a new TV
comedy series depicting the life of an ordinary Beijing resident.
</P>
<P>
Based on the novel "The Happy Life of Zhang Damin, the
Garrulous," the 20-part TV series presents interesting episodes in
the life of a young man living with his large family in a small
single-storey house in one of Beijing's hutongs (narrow lane).
</P>
<P>
The author of the novel, Liu Heng, also wrote the TV version of
his story, according to the Beijing Daily.
</P>
<P>
The novel has already been made into a movie called "A Tree in
the House" which was screened in Beijing and other cities during
the Spring Festival, the Chinese lunar new year festival.
</P>
<P>
Since the movie has been warmly received by audiences across
the country, CCTV and local TV stations in Beijing, Shanghai and
Hunan are anxious to present the TV series.
</P>
<P>
"The story of Zhang represents the lives of many ordinary
people here in our city, and they will personally relate to this
series," said Yin Hong, a professor at Beijing Normal University.
</P>
<P>
The TV series, which combines serious elements with laughter
and tears, is one of the few current TV drama portraying ordinary
people in China in a real way, said TV critic Zhang Yongjing.
</P>
</TEXT>
