<HEADLINE> China Develops Travel Sickness Pill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Chinese military scientists claim
that they have developed a new kind of drug for treating travel
sickness that does not have any side effect unlike most similar
pills.
</P>
<P>
Scientists from the Chinese PLA Medical Research Institute
tested over 10,000 chemical compounds, routinely on animals and in
clinical experiments.
</P>
<P>
The research project has won the state second prize for
invention, the highest-level award for Chinese scientists in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Doctors said travel sickness, which includes sea sickness,
aviation sickness and car sickness, is the stress response during
bumpy motions, which affects people often to great physical
discomfort.
</P>
<P>
Finding a cure which has no side effect has been a high
priority amongst the world's medical elite for some time.
</P>
</TEXT>
