<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Qian Qichen Meets with Yasser Arafat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Palestinian President
Yasser Arafat today briefed Chinese Vice-Premier Qian Qichen on
the latest development in the Middle-East Peace Process.
</P>
<P>
 During their meeting here today, Qian spoke highly of
Arafat's unremitting efforts for the just cause of the Palestinian
people and for the growth of Sino-Palestinian relations.
</P>
<P>
 The Vice-Premier reiterated China's principled position on
the Middle-East issue saying that it is China's consistent policy
to support the just cause of the Palestinian people.
</P>
<P>
 China will continue to support the Middle-East peace process
and the legitimate rights of the Palestinian and Arab people, Qian
noted.
</P>
<P>
 Moreover, he expressed satisfaction with the development of
Sino-Palestinian ties and noted that Arafat's current visit to
China would certainly enhance bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
 Arafat voiced his appreciation for the consistent support of
the Chinese government for the liberation of the Palestinian
people over the past decades.
</P>
<P>
 Arafat and his party arrived here early this morning for a
two-day working visit to China at the invitation of Chinese
President Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin is expected to meet with Arafat and
confer with him on bilateral ties and other issues of common
concern later today. 
</P>
