<HEADLINE> Malaysia to Host World Renewable Energy Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia will host the World
Renewable Energy Congress (WREC) in June this year to promote the
development, adoption and wider utilization of renewable energy
resources globally.
</P>
<P>
Energy, Telecommunications and Multimedia Minister Leo Moggie
told a news conference here Thursday that the WREC to be held
from June 8 to 11 would be the first congress to be held outside
the Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD),
and in Asia.
</P>
<P>
The event will be an activity of the Solar World Program (WSP)
1996-2005, an initiative of the World Solar Commission (WSC) aimed
at promoting the development, adoption and wider utilization of
renewable energy resources globally.
</P>
<P>
June 8 this year would be treated as the "Renewable Energy Day"
for Malaysia with a host of related programs including the
official opening of the Malaysia Energy Center and the flag-off of
the central leg of the Malaysia International Solar Cycle
Challenge by Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad, he said.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia is reviewing its energy strategy to add renewable
energy as the fifth fuel. Currently, Malaysia depends on the four
energy resources -- oil, gas, hydro-power and coal.
</P>
<P>
Leo Moggie said the new five-fuel strategy would be
incorporated in the Eighth Malaysia Plan (2001-2005) which would
mark an important step in the development of a sustainable
national energy policy.
</P>
<P>
Solar and hydro energy, wind and biomass are some of the
renewable energy resources which could be harnessed, Leo Moggie
said, adding renewable energy is increasingly more important now
and technology development and research has progressed so much in
the last few years that the viability of some of the renewable
energy resources are beginning to be seen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
