<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Heritage Study Center Set up in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Prestigious Beijing University (
BU) recently announced the establishment of a new world heritage
research and training center.
</P>
<P>
The center will mainly study both international and national
heritage sites and conduct comparative research into related sites
in different countries. Personnel will receive extensive training
in approaches for studying, evaluating, protecting, planning,
using and managing world-class heritage sites. The center will
also grant master's degrees in related studies.
</P>
<P>
The center will also offer short-term training courses for
workers engaged in management of world-class heritage sites.
</P>
<P>
Xie Ninggao, a professor with Beijing University's Department
of Urban and Environmental Science, will head the center's 26-
member staff of professional researchers, doctorate and other
postgraduate students. The center will also invite specialists to
serve as advisers.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-one Chinese historical sites are included on the
UNESCO's World Heritage List, including the Great Wall, the Palace
Museum or the Forbidden City, Temple of Heaven and Summer Palace
located in Beijing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
