<HEADLINE> Fu Mingxia Confident to Win in National Champion's Tourney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JI'NAN, Shandong Province, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Chinese star
diver Fu Mingxia said here on Thursday that she is confident to
win a title in the National Champion's Tournament, the first major
competition she will take part in after two years in retirement.
</P>
<P>
"Everything is OK," Fu said. "After hard training in the last
few months, I feel more and more confident that I can win."
</P>
<P>
Fu, who won three gold medals in the 1992 and 1996 Olympic
Games, said her confidence was boosted after winning the
qualifying competition for this National Champion's Tournament in
Guangxi last month.
</P>
<P>
She will compete in the three-meter springboard event on Friday.
"If she's good in the event, she may dive in the 10m platform
event on Sunday," said Yu Fen, her long-time coach.
</P>
<P>
"She's made an surprising and quick recovery. Her goal is to
pursue a fourth Olympic gold," Yu said.
</P>
<P>
Yu said that they will take this tournament as a start point of
the march toward the Sydney Olympics. "We take this tournament
very seriously. It's very important to win," Yu said.
</P>
<P>
Fu, 21, who retired after Atlanta Games, resumed training last
summer. Now a student in China's elite Qinghua University, she
hopes to take part in the World University Games to be held in
Spain next August. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
