<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Issues Forest Fire Alert </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 15 (Xinhua)-- The State Forestry Administration
has dispatched seven expert teams to inspect fire prevention
measures in forest areas throughout the nation.
</P>
<P>
An unseasonably warm winter and lingering dry climate resulted
in the outbreak of numerous forest fires nationwide, with a major
fire recently extinguished in north China's Shanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
Some 117 fire-fighters were killed and 237 sustained serious
injuries while battling 78 major forest fires across China during
1998, with the number of deaths dropping by some 74 percent on the
1997 figure.
</P>
<P>
Last year, direct economic losses caused by fires dropped by 27
percent on the 1997 figure to 270 million yuan (33 million US
dollars), according to the Fire Control Department under the
Ministry of Public Security. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
