<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bulgaria Permits Transport of Aid Across Its Territory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The Bulgarian authorities have
agreed to permit a number of countries to transport humanitarian
aid across its territory and air space to Albania, Macedonia and
Yugoslavia, Foreign Ministry spokesman Radko Vlaikov said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
These countries include Turkey, Germany, Great Britain, the
Netherlands, Norway, Austria, Italy, Poland, Greece, Romania,
Hungary, Ukraine, Belarus, Denmark, Slovenia, Sweden and Georgia.
</P>
<P>
The transportation of aid will be subject to strict controls
and checks in compliance with international requirements and
practices, Vlaikov said.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman reiterated Bulgaria's position as it appeared in
the declaration of the Bulgarian parliament and the Bulgarian
government on March 25, which states that Bulgaria will in no way
become involved in the conflict in Yugoslavia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
