<HEADLINE> Czech Republic to Send Field Hospital, Air Freighter to Balkans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The Czech Senate and Chamber of
Deputies approved a bill on Wednesday to send a field hospital and
a noncombatant transport plane to the Balkans to carry out
humanitarian missions.
</P>
<P>
Czech Foreign Minister Jan Karan said the field hospital will
be set up in Albania to operate for about 18 months, with up to
100 volunteers and soldiers working there.
</P>
<P>
He said both the hospital and the plane will be under the
command of NATO.
</P>
<P>
The Czech government also decided on Wednesday to provide 784
million korunas (about 23 million U.S. dollars) to Kosovar
refugees for humanitarian purposes, according to reports of the
Czech news agency.
</P>
<P>
The Czech Republic, a new member of NATO, has always voiced
support for the military action the alliance launched against
Yugoslavia though it has not taken part in the action directly.
</P>
</TEXT>
