<HEADLINE> Shaanxi, Focus of Investment in Northwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Shaanxi Province has become a
strong point for attracting domestic and overseas investment in
northwest China due to its unique geographical location and rich
resources.
</P>
<P>
The province plans to invest 60 billion yuan in fix assets this
year, a 13 percent increase over 1998, to further improve
infrastructure facilities and attract investment from domestic and
overseas businesses.
</P>
<P>
Situated at the crossroads of central and western China,
Shaanxi is playing an important role in helping promote economic
development in northwestern China, provincial governor Chen Andong
said recently.
</P>
<P>
Shaanxi has over 100 colleges, universities and research
institutes and 820,000 technical personnel, and produces more than
2,000 scientific research results annually. In 1998, the
provincial domestic product reached nearly 140 billion yuan, up 9.
3 percent over 1997.
</P>
<P>
A group of domestic and overseas firms have shown interest in
investing in the province at a recently concluded trade fair here,
where there were 131 contracts worth 1.075 billion U.S. dollars in
investment signed, and 127 agreements reached on 2.2 billion U.S.
dollars worth of investment.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Zhongyou Jingxi Scientific and Technological
Development Co. Ltd. signed oil-exploration contracts with three
companies in the province worth an aggregate 30 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The firm's general manager Wang Guozhi said that investing in
Shaanxi will lay a solid foundation for his company's future
development as northwest China has great potential for the oil
industry.
</P>
<P>
Among domestic investors, Jiangsu Province in east China has
plans to invest 100 million yuan to build a large commercial store
in Xi'an, capital of Shaanxi. 
</P>
</TEXT>
