<HEADLINE> Beijing Uses More Overseas Funds in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 15 (Xinhua) -- Beijing used 1.06 billion U.S.
dollars of overseas investment in the first three months of the
year, up 12.4 percent from the first quarter last year.
</P>
<P>
However, information from the municipal statistics bureau said
that the city signed new contracts with overseas investors in the
first quarter which involve promised overseas investment of 390
million U.S. dollars, down 25.8 percent from the first quarter
last year.
</P>
<P>
From January to March this year, 21 large international
companies invested in 25 projects in this national capital, with
contracts worth 128 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
By this March, 438 multinationals and large companies had
invested in 548 projects in Beijing worth 4.519 billion U.S.
dollars of overseas investment. At the same time, 153 of the
world's top 500 companies had started doing business in the
Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
Beijing has so far approved 14,215 overseas-financed ventures
involving 26 billion U.S. dollars of overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
Overseas-backed ventures have been reporting good economic
results. Statistics show that in January and February, 5,464
operational overseas-financed businesses in Beijing generated 82
billion yuan in total industrial output value, up 41 percent over
the same period last year, and realized more than 12 billion yuan
from sales income, up 58.5 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
