issue new bonds totaling one billion yuan (121 million US dollars)
from April 16 to May 5, the Shanghai Securities News said.
</P>
<P>
The maturity of the new bonds will be five years with an annual
interest rate of 5.35 percent. Funds raised by the bonds will be
channeled to construction projects in many parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
A total of 7.6 billion yuan (918 million US dollars) will be
invested in these projects, which include the Minjiang Bridge in
southeast China's Fuzhou City and an airport in south China's
Haikou City.
</P>
<P>
China Everbright Bank is a joint-stock commercial bank with
state-owned companies as its major stockholders. Its pre-tax
profit in 1998 was 1.31 billion yuan, and its per capita profit
was number one among China's domestic banks.  
