<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT April 15 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA -- Turkish military announced here on Wednesday that
nine Russian warships in three batches will pass through Turkish
straits into Adriatic Sea this month.
</P>
<P>
The General Staff of the Turkish Armed Forces said in a
statement that three Russian warships in the first batch will pass
the Canakkale and Bosphorus Straits into the Adriatic Sea between
April 15 and 16, other three in the second batch will pass through
April 18 and 19 and the last three in the third batch will pass
through between April 21 and 22. (Turkey-Russian Ships)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- EgyptAir, Egypt's national carrier, has postponed its
newly-resumed flights to Libya, which was scheduled for Thursday.
</P>
<P>
An Egypt Air source was quoted by the official Middle East News
Agency as saying on Wednesday that the first airliner is expected
to fly to Libya on Sunday if the two countries can solve a number
of commercial issues and decide on the operation schedule. (Egypt-
Libya-Flights)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BELGRADE -- Air raid sirens went off at 20:40 local time
Wednesday over Belgrade, heralding the 22nd night of NATO's
bombing campaign against Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The capital has been quiet during the day except for a strong
explosion at around 10:00 in the morning, followed by air-raid
sirens shortly after. (Yugoslavia-NATO-Bombing)
</P>
