<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Senior Citizen Services Gain Increasing Popularity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The service industry, introduced in March last year, offers
senior citizens a wide variety of activities for an hourly fee of
2.5 yuan (30 US cents).
</P>
<P>
Good living conditions quite often fail to relieve the
loneliness of many senior citizens. "I feel better after
discussing my frustrations." according to one senior citizen named
Yang.
</P>
<P>
Yang, a 70-year-old retiree, has experienced depressing
loneliness due to the fact that his wife passed away and his only
son is busy with his own affairs.
</P>
<P>
Chen Lihui, founder of the service, said that the senior
citizens enjoy simply things such as phone calls.
</P>
<P>
"Our service is quite different from a nursing home which
focuses mainly on spiritual comfort. Most of our staffers are
young people with high-level education and are thus able to
discuss wide-ranging topics." said Chen.
</P>
<P>
Over 400 senior citizens have applied for the service and the
number continues to rise.
</P>
<P>
"Good living conditions do not necessarily bring senior
citizens happiness. Psychological health is also extremely
important," said Chen.
</P>
<P>
Senior citizens accounted for 10 percent of the city's total
population in 1997. Harbin's civil affairs departments have
responded by establishing entertainment centers and various
recreational venues for over 900,000 senior citizens.
</P>
<P>
The service satisfies the needs of senior citizens to
communicate with the younger generation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
