<DOCNO> XIE19990415.0307 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippines' Reserves Hit Record High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 15 (Xinhua) -- The gross international reserves
(GIR) of the Philippine Central Bank hit a new high of 13.196
billion U.S. dollars as of April, up from 12.9 billion U.S.
dollars at the end of March, the Business World reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper quoted the Central Bank Governor Gabriel Singson
as saying late Wednesday that the Central Bank boosted its
reserves by buying dollars "from various sources."
</P>
<P>
The GIR is the central bank's holdings of gold, foreign
exchange, and special drawing rights used to pay the country's
debts and imports.
</P>
<P>
Singson told the newspaper that the Central Bank bought dollars
discreetly so as not to influence the peso-dollar rate. "Every
time there is a buying opportunity, we buy to improve or increase
our reserves, but we buy dollar when it will not heavily influence
the market," Singson said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Central Bank bought "over 1.5 billion" since
the start of the year, but did not provide an exact figure.
</P>
<P>
The country's GIR is now equivalent to 5.4 months' worth of
imports. "These are the highest reserves ever in the history of
the country," Singson said.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine Central Bank has been steadily building up its
reserves after these were depleted when it defended the peso
against speculators at the height of the Asian currency crisis.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990415.0308 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Insurance System Helps Underemployed People in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 15 (Xinhua) -- The unemployment insurance system
is playing a positive role in keeping social stability in China,
with more than three million people benefiting from the system
each year.
</P>
<P>
Established in 1986, the system includes a subsidy fund for the
underemployment in accordance with law, and provides financial aid
and reemployment service to those who lose their jobs through no
fault of their own, according to the Ministry of Labor and Social
Security.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, 79.32 million people, or 45 percent of
the total number of urban employees had been subscribed to the
insurance system, and 12.74 million of them had benefited from the
underemployment subsidies.
</P>
<P>
Since the establishment of the insurance system, labor and
social security departments have been actively involved in setting
up this social insurance fund, and have helped half of all
underemployed people find jobs with financial supports from the
fund.
</P>
<P>
In June 1998, the central government issued a circular raising
the contribution to the unemployment fund from one percent of the
enterprise total payroll to three percent. According to the
circular, enterprises are no longer solely responsible for paying
the fees, but individuals must now contribute one percent.
</P>
<P>
This January, the State Council issued its Regulations on
Unemployment Insurance to initiate several major reforms in the
unemployment insurance fund system, including the method of fund
collection, which will further perfect the system.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
