materials stocks pushed the dow index over 10,500 points for the
first time during the trading. But the index trimmed most of the
gains before the closing as Intel said its revenues from chip
sales might soften in the second quarter after its strong earnings
in the first quarter.
</P>
<P>
the Intel warning about its second quarter earnings turned the
Nasdaq index into the negative territory from the positive one.
The index rose more than 40 points in earlier trading in reaction
to Intel's first quarter earnings report.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index fell 21.38 at 1,328.44 while
the NYSE index fell 6.00 at 625.67.
</P>
<P>
The American Stock Exchange index was down 1.68 to 736.12 but
the Russell 2000 index of smaller companies rose 0.15 to 417.39.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by an 11-to-7 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,769 up, 1,282 down and 532
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume increased to 949.68 million shares from 808.03
million in the previous session. 
